cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

The paper focuses on improving the performance of neuro-evolution techniques for evolving convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for machine learning tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of CNNs for machine learning tasks, which suggests the category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper specifically focuses on convolutional neural networks, which suggests the category cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses potential automation of network design and selection, which suggests the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the use of volunteer computing for gathering results, which suggests the category cs.SY (Systems and Control).
